{"questionId":"21302","questionHtml":"<p>Express <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>z</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mi>z</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mi>z</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math> as a product of linear factors over the set <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℂ</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>z</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>z</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>z</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mi>z</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mi>z</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>considers the equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>z</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mi>z</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mi>z</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>the roots are&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ω</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mi>ω</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mi>ω</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>z</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>ω</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>z</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>ω</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>…</mo>